408
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:46.160
Why?!

409
00:19:46.160 --> 00:19:50.210
No matter where they take Robin,
we'll just follow them until we get her back!

410
00:19:50.210 --> 00:19:53.000
Didn't I explain this
before we left Water Seven?!

411
00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:57.880
The only destinations beyond those gates are
Marine Headquarters and the undersea prison.

412
00:19:58.260 --> 00:20:02.560
We'll need to settle this matter
before they reach them, no matter what.

413
00:20:02.560 --> 00:20:04.560
She's right.

414
00:20:04.560 --> 00:20:08.100
Still, even if we all rush in,

415
00:20:08.100 --> 00:20:11.820
if we encounter CP9, the only ones
who can hope to beat them...

416
00:20:11.820 --> 00:20:13.480
is you guys.

417
00:20:13.480 --> 00:20:17.150
Our time on this train has shown me
just how strong you guys are.

418
00:20:17.150 --> 00:20:20.490
So, you guys wait here
on the sea for five minutes,

419
00:20:20.490 --> 00:20:24.120
then charge through the island's
main gate in Rocketman.

420
00:20:24.120 --> 00:20:28.330
We'll go in first to bust open
the main gate and the island gate.

421
00:20:28.330 --> 00:20:30.710
That way, the train can pass through.

422
00:20:31.130 --> 00:20:36.590
After that, you'll need to keep moving forward,
no matter how many of us fall.

423
00:20:38.720 --> 00:20:41.220
We have just over sixty people,

424
00:20:41.220 --> 00:20:44.560
but our enemy's forces are probably
well above 2,000 or even 3,000.

425
00:20:45.430 --> 00:20:50.980
We'd like you guys to only go after CP9
and avoid any unnecessary battles.

426
00:20:50.980 --> 00:20:52.980
Okay, got it.

427
00:20:52.980 --> 00:20:54.480
Okay, guys!

428
00:20:54.480 --> 00:20:57.150
We just arrived in front of the island!

429
00:20:57.150 --> 00:21:01.070
Take a good look at the sky
behind Enies Lobby.

430
00:21:02.530 --> 00:21:04.910
Those are the Gates of Justice.

431
00:21:04.910 --> 00:21:10.830
– Whoooa! They're huuuge!
– Whoooa! They're huuuge!

432
00:21:13.750 --> 00:21:16.800
They never open all the way.

433
00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:21.840
When criminals are taken through them,
they open just a crack.

434
00:21:22.300 --> 00:21:26.180
Behind those doors is a nest of
giant sea kings just like in the Calm Belt,

435
00:21:26.180 --> 00:21:30.190
the areas of sea that run along
both sides of the Grand Line.

436
00:21:30.560 --> 00:21:33.400
So no ordinary ships venture in there.

437
00:21:33.400 --> 00:21:35.770
I don't know how,

438
00:21:35.770 --> 00:21:39.820
but the Marines have a way to pass
through the gates without being harmed.

439
00:21:39.820 --> 00:21:43.620
In other words, just like the pirate girl said,

440
00:21:43.620 --> 00:21:46.660
if you want to rescue a criminal
who's been brought here,

441
00:21:46.660 --> 00:21:50.410
you've got until the moment
before they go through those gates to do it!

442
00:21:50.410 --> 00:21:53.460
Now, there's no time to lose!

443
00:21:55.960 --> 00:21:58.670
All right! As planned, we're gonna go in first!

444
00:21:59.510 --> 00:22:01.510
We'll cover your entrance!

445
00:22:01.510 --> 00:22:04.720
Hey, you two! Aren't you
supposed to be with us?!

446
00:22:10.180 --> 00:22:11.890
Oh? Where's Luffy?

447
00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:14.520
Huh? He was right here a second ago.

448
00:22:20.690 --> 00:22:21.950
Is that Mr. Straw Hat?

449
00:22:21.950 --> 00:22:23.530
What?!

450
00:22:26.870 --> 00:22:29.330
– What?!
– What?!

451
00:22:29.330 --> 00:22:32.660
Why the hell is he doing things on his own?!

452
00:22:32.660 --> 00:22:35.460
That guy didn't get the plan at all!

453
00:22:37.210 --> 00:22:38.960
So much for that...

454
00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:40.920
He said "got it," didn't he?

455
00:22:40.920 --> 00:22:43.550
It's impossible for him to wait five minutes.

456
00:22:43.550 --> 00:22:45.140
We should've known.

457
00:22:46.970 --> 00:22:49.810
What an impatient guy!

458
00:22:49.810 --> 00:22:52.230
Go! Pirate guy!

459
00:22:56.100 --> 00:22:59.360
Sodom and Gomorrah, don't fall behind!

460
00:22:59.360 --> 00:23:03.030
Climb up the iron fence
and break open the main gate!

461
00:23:06.320 --> 00:23:09.620
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

462
00:23:10.080 --> 00:23:12.450
Gum-Gum...

463
00:23:12.450 --> 00:23:15.040
Rocket!

464
00:23:16.120 --> 00:23:17.080
What was that...?

465
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:20.210
Something just flew by!

466
00:23:24.470 --> 00:23:26.050
What is this place?!

467
00:23:26.050 --> 00:23:27.720
What a huge hole!

468
00:23:27.720 --> 00:23:29.760
It looks like the island is floating.

469
00:23:31.310 --> 00:23:32.770
There's someone up there!

470
00:23:32.770 --> 00:23:35.230
It's an intruder! Shoot him down!

471
00:23:35.940 --> 00:23:37.730
They found me.

472
00:23:40.730 --> 00:23:42.610
He went past the gate!

473
00:23:47.990 --> 00:23:50.280
This is the main gate! This is the main gate!

474
00:23:50.280 --> 00:23:52.580
Reporting to the chief and the island gate!

475
00:23:53.200 --> 00:23:55.830
This is the main gate! Do you copy?!

476
00:23:57.170 --> 00:23:59.330
What is it? What's going on?

477
00:23:59.710 --> 00:24:04.050
An intruder climbed over the main gate
and is rapidly approaching the island gate!

478
00:24:04.050 --> 00:24:07.720
So it's just one intruder.
Calm down and take care of him.

479
00:24:07.720 --> 00:24:08.510
So it's just one intruder.
Calm down and take care of him.

480
00:24:08.510 --> 00:24:10.600
Yes, but...

481
00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:12.510
This is the island gate.

482
00:24:12.510 --> 00:24:14.100
We have eyes on the intruder.

483
00:24:14.100 --> 00:24:16.730
We'll take care of him right away, rest assured.

484
00:24:19.150 --> 00:24:21.730
Hey, kid. Stop this already.

485
00:24:21.730 --> 00:24:23.690
Do you know what this place is?

486
00:24:23.690 --> 00:24:25.610
Do not take him lightly!

487
00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:27.860
Either my eyes deceive me, or that man is...

488
00:24:29.910 --> 00:24:31.620
Straw Hat Luffy!

489
00:24:37.410 --> 00:24:39.540
What?! Can you confirm what you just said?!

490
00:24:39.540 --> 00:24:41.210
I think it's Straw Hat...

491
00:24:42.960 --> 00:24:46.260
a pirate with a 100-million-berry
bounty on his head!

492
00:24:51.430 --> 00:24:52.760
Where's Robin?!

493
00:25:08.280 --> 00:25:12.240
Where the hell is Robin?!
